CHOLERA, DIARRHEA AND DYSENTERY UPDATE (124): ASIA (YEMEN)
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 30 Oct 2017
Source: WHO [edited]
http://www.emro.who.int/images/stories/yemen/Yemen_Cholera_Response_-_Daily_Epidemiological_Update_-_2017-10-29.pdf?ua=1


Cholera Response
----------------
Cumulative figures [27 Apr 2017] to [29 Oct 2017]
884 368: Suspected cases
2184: Associated deaths
0.25 percent: Case Fatality Rate
96 percent: Governorates affected (22/23 governorates)
92 percent: Districts affected (305/333 districts)

[An epidemic curve can be seen at the above URL as well as a breakdown of cases per governorate. The epidemic curve suggests a slow down per week but based on the table below, it is not clear that this is the case. With only 115 632 suspected cases to meet the magic 1 million number, and 116 844 such cases from 29 Sep 2017 to 29 Oct 2017, that number should be exceeded by the end of November 2017. - Mod.LL]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Mary Marshall
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As this horrific story goes on and on, the continuing statistics of this record epidemic of _V. cholerae_ in Yemen are shown below:

