In 2015 http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/250142/1/WER9138.pdf, WHO reported a total of 172 454 cases worldwide in 42 countries.
In 2016 http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/258910/1/WER9236.pdf, the total number of cases was 132 121 from 38 countries.

This continuing, record-breaking cholera disaster in Yemen is only about 6 months old and is 6.7 times the total number of global cases of 2016, and 2.6 times the entire peak year of the Haiti outbreak (2011) of 340 311 cases. The low case fatality rate of 0.26 percent might suggest that some of the diarrhea may be non-cholera. There are now as many cases in 6 months than in the entire 7 years of the Haitian cholera disaster. - Mod.LL

<A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5413552,126.]
